<div id="main">
  <h1 id="title">Tribute page to Stephen Hawking</h1>
      <p><br />Stephen William Hawking, born January 8th, 1942 in Oxford, England. He was an English theoretical physicist, cosmologist, and author. He was famous for his work on physics of black holes, general relativity, and writing a best selling book titled <cite> A Brief History of Time: From the Big Bang to Black Holes</cite>. In the early 1960's Hawking developed an incurable degenerative neuromuscular disease but this never stopped him from working. Hawking died on March 14th, 2018. I found his work and personal story extemely inspiring. For this reason, is why I admire Stephen Hawking. I hope to meet him in another life time.</p>
  
