      <h3><strong>A Brief Biography on Stephen Hawking's life</strong></h3>
       <ul>
        <li><strong>1940's</strong> - Birth and Childhood</li>
        <li><strong>1960's</strong> - Graduated from Oxford and moved to Campbridge</li>
        <li><strong>Mid 60's to early 70's</strong> - Serious career work</li>
        <li><strong>1970's</strong> - He was writing the rulebook for black holes</li>
        <li><strong>1980's</strong> - A health crisis and authorial success</li>
        <li><strong>1990's</strong> - Publishing success</li>
        <li><strong>2000's</strong> - Debates and Bets</li>
        <li><strong>2010's</strong> - "It has been a glorious time to be alive"</li>
      </ul>
      
      <i>"I am an optimist and I believe that we can create AI for the good of the world. That it can work in harmony with us. We simply need to be aware of the dangers, identify them, employ the best possible practice and management, and prepare for its consequences well in advance."</i> <br><br>
      <i>--Web Summit Conference, 2017</i>
